ha Upaniṣad\u003c/em\u003e (1.2.18) we also find a similar passage, which reads:\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"verse_text\",\"id\":595,\"bb\":541,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/20/b541/\",\"body_value\":\"\u003cem\u003ena jāyate mriyate vā vipaścin\u003cbr /\u003enāyaṁ kutaścin na babhūva kaścit\u003cbr /\u003eajo nityaḥ śāśvato ’yaṁ purāṇo\u003cbr /\u003ena hanyate hanyamāne śarīre\u003c/em\u003e\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":596,\"bb\":542,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/20/b542/\",\"body_value\":\"The meaning and purport of this verse is the same as in the \u003cem\u003eBhagavad-gītā,\u003c/em\u003e but here in this verse there is one special word, \u003cem\u003evipaścit,\u003c/em\u003e which means learned or with knowledge.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":597,\"bb\":543,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/20/b543/\",\"body_value\":\"$3b\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":598,\"bb\":544,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/20/b544/\",\"body_value\":\"There are two kinds of souls – namely the minute particle soul (\u003cem\u003eaṇu-ātmā\u003c/em\u003e) and the Supersoul (\u003cem\u003evibhu-ātmā\u003c/em\u003e). This is also confirmed in the \u003cem\u003eKaṭha Upaniṣad\u003c/em\u003e (1.2.20) in this way:\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"verse_text\",\"id\":599,\"bb\":545,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/20/b545/\",\"body_value\":\"\u003cem\u003eaṇor aṇīyān mahato mahīyān\u003cbr /\u003eātmāsya jantor nihito guhāyām\u003cbr /\u003etam akratuḥ paśyati vīta-śoko\u003cbr /\u003edhātuḥ prasādān mahimānam ātmanaḥ\u003c/em\u003e\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":600,\"bb\":546,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/20/b546/\",\"body_value\":\"“Both the Supersoul [Paramātmā] and the atomic soul [ \u003cem\u003ejīvātmā\u003c/em\u003e] are situated on the same tree of the body within the same heart of the living being, and only one who has beco