 is sometimes a necessary factor. Therefore, \u003cem\u003ekṣatriyas\u003c/em\u003e are never meant for accepting directly the order of \u003cem\u003esannyāsa,\u003c/em\u003e or renunciation. Nonviolence in politics may be a diplomacy, but it is never a factor or principle. In the religious law books it is stated:\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"verse_text\",\"id\":680,\"bb\":615,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/31/b615/\",\"body_value\":\"āhaveṣu mitho ’nyonyaṁ\u003cbr /\u003ejighāṁsanto mahī-kṣitaḥ\u003cbr /\u003eyuddhamānāḥ paraṁ śaktyā\u003cbr /\u003esvargaṁ yānty aparāṅ-mukhāḥ\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"verse_text\",\"id\":681,\"bb\":616,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/31/b616/\",\"body_value\":\"yajñeṣu paśavo brahman\u003cbr /\u003ehanyante satataṁ dvijaiḥ\u003cbr /\u003esaṁskṛtāḥ kila mantraiś ca\u003cbr /\u003ete ’pi svargam avāpnuvan\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":682,\"bb\":617,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/31/b617/\",\"body_value\":\"“In the battlefield, a king or \u003cem\u003ekṣatriya,\u003c/em\u003e while fighting another king envious of him, is eligible for achieving the heavenly planets after death, as the \u003cem\u003ebrāhmaṇas\u003c/em\u003e also attain the heavenly planets by sacrificing animals in the sacrificial fire.” Therefore, killing on the battlefield on religious principles and killing animals in the sacrificial fire are not at all considered to be acts of violence, because everyone is benefited by the religious principles involved. The animal sacrificed gets a human life immediately without undergoing the gradual evolutionary process from one form to another, and the \u003cem\u003ekṣatriyas\u003c/em\u003e killed on the battlefield also attain the heavenly planets, as do the \u003cem\u003ebrāhmaṇas\u003c/em\u003e who attain them by offering sacrifice.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":683,\"bb\":618,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/31/b618/\",\"body