\"},{\"word\":\"sāṅkhye\",\"translation\":\"in analytical study\"},{\"word\":\"buddhiḥ\",\"translation\":\"intelligence\"},{\"word\":\"yoge\",\"translation\":\"in work without fruitive result\"},{\"word\":\"tu\",\"translation\":\"but\"},{\"word\":\"imām\",\"translation\":\"this\"},{\"word\":\"śṛṇu\",\"translation\":\"just hear\"},{\"word\":\"buddhyā\",\"translation\":\"by intelligence\"},{\"word\":\"yuktaḥ\",\"translation\":\"dovetailed\"},{\"word\":\"yayā\",\"translation\":\"by which\"},{\"word\":\"pārtha\",\"translation\":\"O son of Pṛthā\"},{\"word\":\"karma-bandham\",\"translation\":\"bondage of reaction\"},{\"word\":\"prahāsyasi\",\"translation\":\"you can be released from\"}]}]},{\"section\":\"translation\",\"section_title\":\"Books.Verse.translation\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"translation\",\"id\":736,\"bb\":663,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/39/b663/\",\"body_value\":\"Thus far I have described this knowledge to you through analytical study. Now listen as I explain it in terms of working without fruitive results. O son of Pṛthā, when you act in such knowledge you can free yourself from the bondage of works.\"}]},{\"section\":\"purport\",\"section_title\":\"Books.Verse.purport\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":737,\"bb\":664,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/39/b664/\",\"body_value\":\"$44\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":738,\"bb\":665,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/39/b665/\",\"body_value\":\"$45\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":739,\"bb\":666,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/39/b666/\",\"body_value\":\"$46\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":740,\"bb\":667,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/39/b667/\",\"body_value\":\"Of course, atheistic \u003cem\u003esāṅkhya-yoga\u003c/em\u003e has nothing to do with \u003cem\u003ebhakti-yoga,\u003c/em\u003e yet the unintelligent claim that the atheistic \u003cem\u003esāṅkhya-yoga\u003c/em\u003e is referred to in the \u003cem\u003eBhagavad-gītā.\u003c/em\u003e\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":741,\"bb\":668,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/39/b668/\",\"body_value\":\"One should therefore understand that \u003cem\u003ebuddhi-yoga\u003c/em\u003e means to work in Kṛṣṇa consciousness, in the full bliss and knowledge of devotional service. One who works for the satisfaction of the Lord only, however difficult such work may be, is working under the principles of \u003cem\u003ebuddhi-yoga\u003c/em\u003e and finds himself always in transcendental bliss. By such transcendental engagement, one achieves all transcendental understanding automatically, by the grace of the Lord, and thus his liberation is complete in itself, without his making extraneous endeavors to acquire knowledge. There is much difference between work in Kṛṣṇa consciousness and work for fruitive results, especially in the matter of sense gratification for achieving results in terms of family or material happiness. \u003cem\u003eBuddhi-yoga\u003c/em\u003e is therefore the transcendental quality of the work that we perform.\"}]}],\"short_title\":\"Bg. 2.39\",\"medium_title\":\"Bhagavad-gītā As It Is 2.39\"},{\"id\":742,\"meta\":{\"type\":\"books.Verse\",\"slug\":\"40\",\"show_in_menus\":false,\"seo_title\":\"\",\"search_description\":\"\",\"first_published_at\":null,\"alias_of\":null,\"locale\":\"en\"},\"title\":\"TEXT 40\",\"advanced_view_url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/advanced-view/#bb669\",\"language_menu\":[{\"display_name\":\"አማርኛ (Ethiopian)\",\"language_code\":\"am\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/am/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Български (Bulgarian)\",\"language_code\":\"bg\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/bg/library/bg/2/40/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Čeština (Czech)\",\"language_code\":\"cs\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/cs/library/bg/2/40/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Dansk (Danish)\",\"language_code\":\"da\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/