iscrimination who is endeavoring to control them.\"}]},{\"section\":\"purport\",\"section_title\":\"Books.Verse.purport\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":886,\"bb\":795,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/60/b795/\",\"body_value\":\"There are many learned sages, philosophers and transcendentalists who try to conquer the senses, but in spite of their endeavors, even the greatest of them sometimes fall victim to material sense enjoyment due to the agitated mind. Even Viśvāmitra, a great sage and perfect \u003cem\u003eyogī,\u003c/em\u003e was misled by Menakā into sex enjoyment, although the \u003cem\u003eyogī\u003c/em\u003e was endeavoring for sense control with severe types of penance and \u003cem\u003eyoga\u003c/em\u003e practice. And, of course, there are so many similar instances in the history of the world. Therefore, it is very difficult to control the mind and senses without being fully Kṛṣṇa conscious. Without engaging the mind in Kṛṣṇa, one cannot cease such material engagements. A practical example is given by Śrī Yāmunācārya, a great saint and devotee, who says:\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"verse_text\",\"id\":887,\"bb\":796,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/60/b796/\",\"body_value\":\"\u003cem\u003eyad-avadhi mama cetaḥ kṛṣṇa-pādāravinde\u003cbr /\u003enava-nava-rasa-dhāmany udyataṁ rantum āsīt\u003cbr /\u003etad-avadhi bata nārī-saṅgame smaryamāne\u003cbr /\u003ebhavati mukha-vikāraḥ suṣṭhu niṣṭhīvanaṁ ca\u003c/em\u003e\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":888,\"bb\":797,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/60/b797/\",\"body_value\":\"“Since my mind has been engaged in the service of the lotus feet of Lord Kṛṣṇa, and I have been enjoying an ever new transcendental humor, whenever I think of sex life with a woman, my face at once turns from it, and I spit at the thought.”\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":889,\"bb\":798,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/60/b798/\",\"body_value\":\"Kṛṣṇa consciousness is such a transcendentally nice thing that automatically material enjoyment becomes distasteful. It is as if a hungry man had satisfied his hunger by a sufficient quantity of nutritious eatables. Mahārāja Ambarīṣa also conquered a great \u003cem\u003eyogī,\u003c/em\u003e Durvāsā Muni, simply because his mind was engaged in Kṛṣṇa consciousness (\u003cem\u003esa vai manaḥ kṛṣṇa-padāravindayor vacāṁsi vaikuṇṭha-guṇānuvarṇane\u003c/em\u003e).\"}]}],\"short_title\":\"Bg. 2.60\",\"medium_title\":\"Bhagavad-gītā As It Is 2.60\"},{\"id\":890,\"meta\":{\"type\":\"books.Verse\",\"slug\":\"61\",\"show_in_menus\":false,\"seo_title\":\"\",\"search_description\":\"\",\"first_published_at\":null,\"alias_of\":null,\"locale\":\"en\"},\"title\":\"TEXT 61\",\"advanced_view_url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/advanced-view/#bb799\",\"language_menu\":[{\"display_name\":\"አማርኛ (Ethiopian)\",\"language_code\":\"am\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/am/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Български (Bulgarian)\",\"language_code\":\"bg\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/bg/library/bg/2/61/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Čeština (Czech)\",\"language_code\":\"cs\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/cs/library/bg/2/61/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Dansk (Danish)\",\"language_code\":\"da\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/da/library/bg/2/61/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Deutsch (German)\",\"language_code\":\"de\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/de/library/bg/2/61/\"},{\"display_name\":\"English\",\"language_code\":\"en\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/2/61/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Español (Spanish)\",\"language_code\":\"es\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/es/library/bg/2/61/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Eesti keel (Estonian)\",\"language_code\":\"et\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/et/library/bg/2/61/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Suomen kieli (Finnish)\",\"language_code\":\"fi\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/fi/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Français (French)\",\"language_code\":\"fr\",