lace. Take, for example, a big skyscraper manifested from the earth. When it is dismantled, the manifestation becomes again unmanifested and remains as atoms in the ultimate stage. The law of conservation of energy remains, but in course of time things are manifested and unmanifested – that is the difference. Then what cause is there for lamentation either in the stage of manifestation or in unmanifestation? Somehow or other, even in the unmanifested stage, things are not lost. Both at the beginning and at the end, all elements remain unmanifested, and only in the middle are they"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1," manifested, and this does not make any real material difference.e5:[\"$\",\"div\",\"651-purport,651-purport\",{\"className\":\"av-purport\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4\",\"children\":\"Purport\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L59\",\"child-656\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:27:child_items:4:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$1d3\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L59\",\"child-657\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:27:child_items:4:children:1\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"And if we accept the Vedic conclusion as stated in the \u003cem\u003eBhagavad-gītā\u003c/em\u003e that these material bodies are perishable in due course of time (\u003cem\u003eantavanta ime dehāḥ\u003c/em\u003e) but that the soul is eternal (\u003cem\u003enityasyoktāḥ śarīriṇaḥ\u003c/em\u003e), then we must remember always that the body is like a dress; therefore why lament the changing of a dress? The material body has no factual existence in relation to the eternal soul. It is something like a dream. In a dream we may think of flying in the sky, or sitting on a chariot as a king, but when we wake up we can see that we are neither in the sky nor seated on the chariot. The Vedic wisdom encourages self-realization on the basis of the nonexistence of the material body. Therefore, in either case, whether one believes in the existence of the soul or one does not believe in the existence of the soul, there is no cause for lamentation for loss of the body.\"}}]}]]]}]\ne6:[\"$\",\"div\",\"658-devanagari,658-devanagari\",{\"className\":\"av-devanagari\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidden\",\"children\":\"Devanagari\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L59\",\"child-659\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:28:child_"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"items:0:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-lg text-center\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"आश्चर्यवत्पश्यति कश्चिदेन -\u003cbr/\u003eमाश्चर्यवद्वदति तथैव चान्यः ।\u003cbr/\u003eआश्चर्यवच्च‍ैनमन्यः श‍ृणोति\u003cbr/\u003eश्रुत्वाप्येनं वेद न चैव कश्चित् ॥ २९ ॥\"}}]}]]]}]\ne7:[\"$\",\"div\",\"658-verse_text,658-verse_text\",{\"className\":\"av-verse_text\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidden\",\"children\":\"Verse text\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L59\",\"child-660\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:28:child_items:1:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base text-center italic\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"\u003cem\u003eāścarya-vat paśyati kaścid enam\u003cbr /\u003eāścarya-vad vadati tathaiva cānyaḥ\u003cbr /\u003eāścarya-vac cainam anyaḥ śṛṇoti\u003cbr /\u003eśrutvāpy enaṁ veda na caiva kaścit\u003c/em\u003e\"}}]}]]]}]\n"])</script>