em\u003e in Kṛṣṇa consciousness, whereas the nondevotee rejects it as material. The impersonalist, therefore, cannot enjoy life, due to his artificial renunciation; and for this reason, a slight agitation of the mind pulls him down again into t"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"he pool of material existence. It is said that such a soul, even though rising up to the point of liberation, falls down again due to his not having support in devotional service.18f:[\"$\",\"div\",\"907-purport,907-purport\",{\"className\":\"av-purport\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4\",\"children\":\"Purport\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L59\",\"child-912\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:61:child_items:4:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"Śrīla Rūpa Gosvāmī has given us this direction:\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L59\",\"child-913\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:61:child_items:4:children:1\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base text-center italic\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"\u003cem\u003eprāpañcikatayā buddhyā\u003cbr /\u003ehari-sambandhi-vastunaḥ\u003cbr /\u003emumukṣubhiḥ parityāgo\u003cbr /\u003evairāgyaṁ phalgu kathyate\u003c/em\u003e\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L59\",\"child-914\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:61:child_items:4:children:2\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base text-right\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"(\u003cem\u003eBhakti-rasāmṛta-sindhu\u003c/em\u003e 1.2.258)\u003cem\u003e\u003c/em\u003e\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L59\",\"child-915\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_